sales_multiple_units <-
  sales_all_boroughs |>
  filter(sale_price > 0) |>
  group_by(bldg_address) |>
  summarize(
    num_units = n(),
    num_prices = n_distinct(sale_price),
    num_dates = n_distinct(sale_date)
  ) |>
  filter(num_units > 1)

sales_entire_bldg <-
  sales_multiple_units |>
  filter(
    num_units > 1 &
      num_dates == 1
  )
pluto_data <-
  read_csv(
    file = "../data/pluto/Primary_Land_Use_Tax_Lot_Output__PLUTO_.csv",
    # Guess column type based on more rows than default
    guess_max = 120000
  ) |>
  filter(address %in% sales_all_boroughs_filter$bldg_address) |>
  # Select columns and create tidy column names
  select(
    borough,
    bbl,
    address_pluto = address,
    ct2010 = `census tract 2010`,
    cb2010,
    community_dist = `community board`,
    council_dist = `council district`,
    res_area = resarea,
    num_floors = numfloors,
    year_built_pluto = yearbuilt,
    year_altered_1 = yearalter1,
    year_altered_2 = yearalter2,
    historic_dist = histdist,
    landmark,
    latitude,
    longitude
  )

# Individual sales

point_map_data <-
  all_data |>
  # Most recent sales first
  arrange(
    sale_date |>
      desc()
  ) |>
  # Preserve only one sale per BBL
  # arrange() call above preserves most recent
  distinct(
    bbl,
    .keep_all = TRUE
  )

point_map_data <-
  point_map_data |>
  mutate(
    # Create legible neighborhood names
    address_title = 
      str_to_title(address),
    # Create legible neighborhood names
    neighborhood_title = 
      str_to_title(neighborhood),
    # Format sale prices to readable style
    sale_price_dollar =
      sale_price |>
      scales::dollar(),
    # Create label
    label = 
      str_c(
        "<p> <b>",
        address_title,
        "</b> </br>",
        "Neighborhood:",
        neighborhood_title,
        "</br>",
        "Sale price:",
        sale_price_dollar,
        "</p>",
        sep = " "
      )
  )
# Leaflet map of all sales

leaflet(
    point_map_data,
    width = 1280,
    height = 720
  ) |>
  addProviderTiles(
    providers$Stamen.Toner,
    options = 
    tileOptions(
      minZoom = 10, # furthest
      maxZoom = 18 # closest
    )
  ) |>
  addCircles(
    ~longitude,
    ~latitude,
    color =
      ~colorBin(
        palette = "viridis",
        log(sale_price)
      )(log(sale_price)),
    weight = 5,
    opacity = 1.0,
    popup = ~label
  )
